      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but it still feels like you're saying the legal arguments are basically secondary. if the data shows a law would save lives, shouldn't the priority be on the actual life-saving potential rather than getting stuck on constitutional interpretations? isn't the \"correct\" path basically just following what the data says?",
